<br>
Her mind was floating around her. Her target was close, she could feel it. All she had been told was that it was female. A buzzing shot through her head; it was very close... Her feet picked up and she began to jog. This would be a peice of cake, just like the rest of the assignments had been. Peice of ca- a shrill scream deafened her ears. There, right in front of her stood a busty blonde with cream white skin in a rather revealing red top and black skirt waiting to cross the street. The scream grew louder forcing her not to hesitate. The fallen angel grabbed for her right hands dagger and as she did so, lunged forward at the blonde. It was quick. In one graceful swipe the target had its hands clutching the deep wound just below its hip before its leg began. There was no saving this target. <br>
Just as quickly as she had attacked, the once angel was gone. Her boots made no sound as she ran from the scene. But the pain of the scream had long since subsided. The moment her blade made contact with skin it had stopped. A dark ally's fire escape was the refuge she found. Crouched on the tip of her toes she sat with the wheels in her head turning. Not a drop of blood tainted her white outfit. It was the blade that was stained. She didn't mind the killing, not anymore. But why did she continue to do it? She wasn't looking for re-entry into the place she had once lived. It wasn't redemtion she was after. So then, why? To be human? No, being a fallen angel had many advantages. Maybe... she did it so that she could kill... and justify it? Or perhaps... yes, perhaps it was simply that she's forgotten her reasons in all the blood, and now the only thing left is the mechanical completion of her tasks. What happened to what little life she had? It was gone. All there was for her was the assignments. She wasn't living... she was working. <p><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
