Standing in the street, Vermifax watched with a slight grin the fiend tear the lady apart. Looking up he saw the sky and the stars. Many couldn't see their luster, for the city had bloated out their once mighty strength. Standing below the lamp light, looking at his watch, the angel. He had made a promise. For his life, he must give up a fallen angel. He would find her and he would kill her, just as he had in the past. It seemed that his cowerdly heart had taken over once more. Again looking at the fiend, he let his frustration out on the lamp light and lifted back to his normal perch on the cross above St. Mary's church. The girl, the angel, the same. Angry now, Vermifax looked out into the city. His thoughts concentrated on the soft flicks of emotion from a strong being. There she was. She was sitting in an ally. He hated himself, maybe she would be strong enough, maybe she wouldn't. He only hoped that this would be the last. Floating down to the city below, his tail flexed and his claws grew slightly longer. Why did he not just let the hunters kill him in the beginning. Now he would be passed down as their slave forever. Closing his eyes he saw the figure sitting. Even from here her perfection and beauty was as obvious to Vermifax as were his constalations in the skys. Maybe he could tell her that she needed to leave town... maybe he could tell her to go somewhere that they wouldn't find her... He'd have to face the hunter of course. As he landed next to the angel, he pushed all thoughts out of his mind, he had a job to do.<br>
Human form again, &quot;Hello there.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
you're partner in crime<br>
