Inside the elevator, Vermifax felt nothing, not a single emotion. He was hungry. letting the doors open he didn't wait for his hostess to come get the door. He walked straight into the room. Walking around the house, he didn't see anyone, but he could feel a pressence. &quot;Little girl. Come out, there's no point in delaying this.&quot; The edge in his voice was gone, he was nothing but a hungry hollow shell. &quot;Don't make this hard on either of us. I want to end this. GET YOUR ASS OUT HERE NOW!&quot; he roared finally not able to take it anymore. He needed to do this. He stormed from room to room till he found her. Sitting her back to him staring at a wall. He could do this easy. He could. Stareing at her back, the twin scars ran verticlly downwards. His tail started to extend. The ball at the end, the spikes. He looked at her neck, long slender, perfect. He was destroying a divine being... no he was going to destroy a cast down demon. He started forward. No... shaking his head he stopped. She still hadn't turned, was she that scared, or was she simply that indifferent. If it the first it would be usual, but if the second. He knew he couldn't take the life. &quot;Turn around atleast and tell me your name? Please?&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
your partner in crime<br>
