sy for her to make the first move. And she did... Her eyes drifted up him, looked right through him until granite iris's stared directly into his eyes. In his mind, the world melted away. All that was was her slate grey eyes. She leaned her head to the side, and as the world began to drip back into view, he watched her blankly as she pulled her hair from her shoulder so her bare neck was before him. A single swipe of a claw, a small gash from a blade, and stab, a wound, and she was gone. His job would be done then. But before him stood an angel, forfieting her life to him. She was allowing him to take her essance... it was the ultimate submission. An Angel... submissing? ...to an imp. <p><br>
