<br>
<br>
<br>
Throwing his vision back to the angel. Vermifax was not worried about the hunter. He had dealt with those before, but he had never taken a fully fed Fiend. &quot;Oh!&quot; He didn't want the girl to be hurt, and he pounced at the fiend as a strike was aimed at his back. he growled but did not turn. His claws were so close, his tail ready to rip. All his rage was going for one thing, kill. His vision was red and he could taste the blood of those who threatened on his hunt! <br>
